snippet.textDisplay: Cats on stage was a musical dance review. It had no plot. It was a book of poems set to music by Andrew Lloyd Weber by T.S. Elliott. What did anyone expect in a movie? In 1998 they filmed a version in a backlot of what was pretty much the stage show with dancers in costumes, with the original choreography and recreated stage look of the garbage junkyard. You’ve made this a joke. The movie came out badly. Amongst how many other bad movies that studios have put out. I’m not defending it but Cats was always going to be divisive. It’s not a horror show. It’s not Dante’s 10th level of hell. It just had many faults but was not the crime of the century.
